Huw Stephens introduces Los Angeles rock funk legends Red Hot Chili Peppers
as they return to headline the legendary Reading Festival. This is the fourth
time the band have headlined the festival since their debut top slot back in
1994 and comes after the release of their first studio album in five years,
The Getaway, which recently topped the charts around the world.

Hailing as one of the biggest American bands of the 80s, the roots of the
group lie in a friendship forged by school friends singer Anthony Kiedis,
guitarist Hillel Slovak, bassist Flea and drummer Jack Irons. They quickly
rose to fame in 1983 and went on to gain huge success right from the release
of their self-titled debut in 1984. After various line-ups with musicians
joining, leaving and rejoining, over the course of 33 years the Red Hot Chili
Peppers have released 11 studio albums, three live albums and 43 singles...
